'''Siân Phillips''' born '''Jane Elizabeth Ailwên Phillips''' in [[Wikipedia:Gwaun-Cae-Gurwen|Gwaun-Cae-Gurwen]], [[Wikipedia:Wales|Wales]], is a [[Wikipedia:Wales|Welsh]] actress. She played [[Charal]] in the [[1985]] made-for-TV film ''[[Ewoks: The Battle for Endor]]''.

Phillips is best known for once being married to Peter O'Toole and her performance as Roman empress Livia in the British miniseries [[Wikipedia:I, Claudius (TV series)|''I, Claudius'']] (the wife of [[Brian Blessed]]'s Emperor Augustus). She also appeared as the Reverend Mother [[Wikipedia:Gaius Helen Mohiam|Gaius Helen Mohiam]] in David Lynch's science-fiction epic [[Wikipedia:Dune (film)|''Dune'']]. In the BBC miniseries adaptions of [[Wikipedia:Tinker, Tailor, Soldier, Spy|''Tinker, Tailor, Soldier, Spy'']] and [[Wikipedia:Smiley's People|''Smiley's People'']], she plays the wife of [[Alec Guinness]]' character.

In [[2000]], Phillips was awarded the honorary title of [[Wikipedia:Order of the British Empire|Commander of the British Empire]] for services to drama.

